# Deploy: image naming (GHCR)

Use when editing compose or `.env.prod` in the deploy repo. Pick one pattern per project and stick to it.

## Preferred: package per project (one GHCR package per app)

```
ghcr.io/<org>/<project>/backend:latest
ghcr.io/<org>/<project>/frontend:latest
ghcr.io/<org>/<project>/backend-<role>:latest   # for extra backends
```

Example: `ghcr.io/husamay/tiktoksearch/backend:latest`, `ghcr.io/husamay/tiktoksearch/backend-urlresolver:latest`

## Alternative: package per image (one GHCR package per service)

```
ghcr.io/<org>/<project>-backend:latest
ghcr.io/<org>/<project>-frontend:latest
```

Example: `ghcr.io/husamay/newswebsite-backend:latest`, `ghcr.io/husamay/flameforge-frontend:latest`

## Env vars and defaults

- **In .env.prod:** `PROJECT_BACKEND_IMAGE`, `PROJECT_FRONTEND_IMAGE`, `PROJECT_BACKEND_<ROLE>_IMAGE` (UPPERCASE, underscores).
- **Default in compose:** Match whatever the app's CI pushes. Override via `.env.prod` if the app uses different names.
